Style of text:
 = Inline: <h2 style="color: blue">Text</h2>
 = Handle style in on go on the top of your page (called CSS): 
    <style>                
      h2 {color: red;}    | Important: opening and closing curly braces ({ and }) around each element's style
    </style>              | and each element ends with semicolon.
 = Creat classes (Formatvorlagen)  
    <style>
      .blue-text {        | Make sure, classes start with a period.
        color: blue;      
      }                    ==> <h2 class="blue-text">CatPhotoApp</h2>
  
      h1 {
        font-size: 30px;
      }
   </style>

<!-- Import font from Google, Set Font Family as Lobster, Monospace ist "Reserve", falls Lobster nicht geht. -->

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lobster" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
<style>
  .red-text {
    color: red;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: Lobster, Monospace;
  }
